snippet.textDisplay: Don't overlook the huge amounts of subsidies provided to the meat and dairy industry ($38 billion per year). This accounts for the difference in price between animal products and these popular plant-based alternatives. In my opinion, another effective way to cause change and to protect Earth, in addition to eating less meat and dairy, would be to elect government officials who would reconsider the amount of subsidies given to the meat and dairy industry. This would increase price and less would choose to consume it. I think we should also think of the farmers and their livelihood. As this transition takes place (animal to plant-based), we should consider offering programs of support to farmers as they consider viable plant farming options. Anyways, those were a few of my thoughts. Great video, Mark! Thanks for spreading awareness.
snippet.textOriginal: Don't overlook the huge amounts of subsidies provided to the meat and dairy industry ($38 billion per year). This accounts for the difference in price between animal products and these popular plant-based alternatives. In my opinion, another effective way to cause change and to protect Earth, in addition to eating less meat and dairy, would be to elect government officials who would reconsider the amount of subsidies given to the meat and dairy industry. This would increase price and less would choose to consume it. I think we should also think of the farmers and their livelihood.
